{"cursor":"11588","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox scientist |name = Sean M. Carroll |image = Seanmcarroll2.jpg\n|image_size = 269px |caption = Sean Carroll |birth_date = |birth_place =\nPhiladelphia, Pennsylvania |death_date = |death_place = |residence = Los\nAngeles, California |citizenship = |nationality = United States |ethnicity =\n|fields = Physics, Cosmology, Astrophysics, General Relativity |workplaces =\nCalifornia Institute of Technology |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = George B.\nField |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = Ignacy Sawicki |notable_students\n= |known_for = |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = Albert\nEinstein, Ludwig Boltzmann |influenced = |awards = |spouse = Jennifer Ouellette\n|religion = Atheism |signature =  |footnotes = }} 'Sean\nMichael Carroll', Ph.D. (born 5 October 1966) is a senior research associate in\nthe Department of Physics at the California Institute of Technology. He is a\ntheoretical cosmologist specializing in dark energy and general relativity. He\nis also a contributor to the physics blog Cosmic Variance, and has published in\nscientific journals and magazines such as ''Nature'', ''Seed'', [[Sky &\nTelescope]], and [[New Scientist]].\n\nDescribed as a gifted science communicator, he has appeared on the\nHistory Channel's ''The Universe'', Science Channel's ''Through the Wormhole\nwith Morgan Freeman'', and Comedy Central's [[The Colbert Report]]. Carroll is\nthe author of Spacetime And Geometry, a graduate-level textbook in general\nrelativity, and has also recorded lectures for The Great Courses on cosmology\nand the physics of time. [http://www.thegreatcourses.com/tgc/professors/pr-\nofessor_detail.aspx?pid=339 Sean Carroll profile page at\nTheGreatCourses.com] He is also the author of two popular books: one on\nthe arrow of time entitled From Eternity to\nHere, [http://preposterousuniverse.com/eternitytohere/\nPreposterousuniverse.com] and one on the Higgs boson